    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 PW/3–2946</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Officer in Charge of the Office of the
                            Political Adviser in Japan</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 340</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-29">March 29,
                            1946</date>.<lb/>[Received April 8.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Officer in Charge has the honor to forward copies, in quadruplicate, of a
                    memorandum from the Supreme Commander for the Allied Powers to the Japanese
                    Government, dated March 16, 1946,<note n="48" xml:id="d172fn1">
                        <gloss target="#t_Scapin1">Scapin</gloss>–822, not printed.</note> which
                    sets forth basic instructions covering the repatriation of Japanese nationals
                    from the areas of the various military commanders in the Far East and of
                    displaced persons in Japan formerly domiciled in China, Formosa, and the
                    Ryukyus. This directive supersedes all previous instructions to the Japanese
                    Government on the general subject of repatriation.</p>
                <p>It will be noted that the directive will not apply to the repatriation of
                    Japanese nationals from the areas under the military control of the Commander in
                    Chief of Soviet Forces in the Far East until appropriate agreements have been
                    consummated.</p>
            </div>
